subject_prompt_600: Tsubasa: Reservoir Chronicle is a manga by Yoshihiro Togashi that has been serialized from 1999 to 2004, with a final volume published on October 9th 2015. The series follows the everyday life of Tsubasa Sakuraba, a 16 year old boy who gets accepted into Shokugeki no Soma, a school that is comprised of over 1,200 different classes and offers students with amazing odds at a chance to enter the elite, prestigious academy.
coupled_prompt_600:
Cardcaptor Sakura universe. An anime based on a Japanese children's manga series, which focuses on the daily life of a little sister and her two younger sisters, who are also young girls. In the story, they come to live with their aunt, and she takes care of them while their parents are gone.

Cardcaptor Sakura: The Beautiful World. An anime directed by Kazuhiro Furukawa, which features the voices of many of the main characters.

Cardcaptor Sakura: The Movie: The Day the Sakura Cry. An anime directed by Kenji Nojima that follows Sakura and the others after the defeat of Gokai Red.

Cardcaptor Sakura: The Movie 2: The Silver Wings. An anime directed by Tomohiro Suzuki that follows Sakura after the events of the second movie.
